						<summary>

						<p>This is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Prabhava, Āshāḍha, ba. 15, Bṛihavāra,</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1207 July 26, Thursday</hi> in the reign of the Hoysaḷa king <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Ballāḷa (II).</hi> Unfortunately the record is damaged. All that can be gathered is that, under the presidency of <hi rend="bold">Vishṇukara-Brahmachāri,</hi> a learned ascetic, the five <hi rend="italic">Vargas,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">Eḷkōṭi-Mahādēvas,</hi> the numberless <hi rend="italic">gaṇas</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">Mummuridaṇḍas</hi> assembled together and resolved that breach of conduct and offences should be referred to the local <hi rend="italic">tapōdhana i.e.,</hi> Vishṇukara-Brahmachāri.</p>						

						</summary>
